'''Zulkifli bin Hir''', also known by the name '''Marwan''', was a top leader of the [[al Queda]] related [[Jemaa Islamiya]] terror network in the [[Philippines]]. He gained international notoriety when he was killed in a U.S.-backed airstrike on 2 February 2012. The U.S. had offered a five million dollar reward for his capture. It was reported the day after he was killed in airstrikes that his body had not been found.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boston.com/news/world/asia/articles/2012/02/02/philippines_most_wanted_terror_leaders_killed/|title=AP: Filipino troops still search for terrorist|author=Hrvoje Hranjski and Jim Gomez|date=2 February 2012}}</ref>

